    "description": "Budapest, often called the 'Pearl of the Danube', is Hungary's capital and largest city, renowned for its therapeutic thermal baths and stunning architecture. The city is divided by the Danube River into Buda and Pest, each offering distinct experiences. From the historic Buda Castle and Fisherman's Bastion to the iconic Hungarian Parliament Building and Chain Bridge, Budapest showcases a rich architectural heritage. The city's famous thermal baths, like Széchenyi and Gellért, offer a unique wellness experience dating back to Roman times. Budapest's vibrant café culture, world-class museums, and lively ruin bars make it a perfect blend of history and contemporary urban life.",
